title.narrative: HEALTH NORTH SYRIA

description.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical health needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP, which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: MENARO delivers timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action as a complement to country office-led operations where required, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.

title.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical health needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP

description.narrative: Despite the heavy shelling that targeted health facilities in North West Syria (NWS), UNICEF has continued delivering essential health services in strategic areas to ensure equity and access. UNICEF supported essential primary and secondary health services for 227,931 people, 2 polio vaccination campaign that reached 867,952 children under 5 as well as a routine EPI programme that delivered DPT3 vaccine for 108,899 children under 1. A total of 922,660 caregivers and guardians received health promotion messages to improve the health status of their children and 29 professionals were trained on Neonatal Resuscitation techniques | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/04/2020
